The paper deals with the problem of matching ground-level and aerial images, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The proposed method involves the use of conditional GANs, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer graphics (cs.MM). The paper also discusses feature learning and feature fusion, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.GR, followed by cs.LG, cs.MM, and cs.AI.
